remark: Easy v3 (especially for Joshua Tree).
Cool arete on the wedge boulder
Crux on the 3rd and 4th bolt. Delicate moves and a side pull with the right hand on a sketchy gaston brings you through the crux.
Pretty good
Tough start
Very tough start!!!
Short route with very physical moves. Nice climb.
Tried top roping, but couldn't get the crux kneebar move.
Pretty easy 10a with a committing move on the 5th bolt.
Very cool climb, definitely want to redpoint this.

Pretty nice climb, with two cruxes: 1 on the third and fourth bolt on the overhang, 2 on the last move to the top. The top crux is still iffy to me what exactly to use for the beta. I'm pretty sure I could have redpointed if I didn't have to leave, the sun was setting.
Pretty fun climb, easy after pulling up out of the overhang.up outverhang

Pumpy short route with some hard moves, overhang from top to bottom, hard to get a rest. Final move is very sick -- from last bolt to top goes from overhang to extra-overhang, and requires a slick dynamic move to the final jug. I attempted twice, second attempt only fell once.
Decent

Overhang middle section is challenging with small holds on the hump, push through the hump to get to jugs for a good rest. Final move to the top is mad hard -- sloper to a crimp, pinch the tufa to clip the top. pumped!
Technical

Long climb, full of adventure, including a section covered in bat urine. I worked hard and diligently to make it to the top cleanly, only to fall on the last bolt before the chains. Very dissapointed. Also -- turns out our 70m rope was more like 62m, so I had to downclimb (or, uhm, daisy-chain solo) down from the 4th bold.

It was raining today, the second bolt was very, very sketchy as a result of the rain. This route is mostly protected from the rain, but there are still some parts where it seeps through cracks in the rock. Other than the second bolt, it was an enjoyable climb. Pumpy! Final bolt to the top was done 100% on faith, due to pumpiness. When you fall due to "pump", or tirendess in the arms, that is 100% due to a mental limit, NOT physical limit. This route proved that to me. You just need to overcome your mental limit.

Tried this 3 times today. First time was a mess -- resting on 3rd bolt, 4th bolt, and 5th bolt. Second time I gave it a serious attempt, had my mental game on lock, but still was absolutely gutted on 5th bolt and had to take. Probably could have pushed through. Third attempt was a regression -- I fell on the second bolt! Luckily Chyah caught me just fine. Rested again on 4th and 5th bolt. Guh. Gonna have to come back for the redpoint on this one. BTW -- some people say this is 5.10d, some say 5.11a if you climb the outer line on the big flake (rather than going up behind the flake).
Hung this route for our beginner friends. Was kind of a cool thrill due to the first two bolts being basically covered in mud. Cool tall climb.
Fucking perverted route. Really uncomfortable technical climbing over weird bumps. Some cool boulder moves in the beginning, though.

Cool roof climb. My first time touching 5.12 and I was surprised I could actually do a lot of the moves. Not super comfortable with the overhang, though, so I only got about halfway through both times I tried.
Tried top roping. Wtf. Hard and scary.
Cool roof climb. Did not send because it's too hard, but want to come back and send
